  "market_context": "ETH was in an hourly consolidation range; price broke the low, then expanded through the high, forming an hourly fair value gap. Analyst identified a bullish continuation setup aligned with HTF bias, using candle 3 closure and swing point confirmation.",
  "key_observation": "After breaking the consolidation range high, ETH formed an hourly gap (internal to external liquidity), and a candle 3 closure on the 15-minute chart confirmed a bullish continuation into the new hourly candle open.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identified an hourly consolidation range that was taken out on the low, then expanded through the high, creating an hourly fair value gap (internal to external).",
    "Step 2: Noted the new hourly candle opening at noon and looked for continuation inside candle 3 or 4 of the hourly structure.",
    "Step 3: Dropped to the 15-minute timeframe to locate a swing point and confirmed a candle 2 closure (initially weak) followed by a stronger candle 3 engulfing pattern that validated the reversal.",
    "Step 4: Verified EQ (equilibrium) was respected and positioned for long entries at the open of the new hourly candle, anticipating open-low-high-close delivery.",
    "Step 5: Went down to the 1-minute chart, cleared drawings, observed a protected swing below EQ, and identified two viable entry zones: (a) close-through of the 15m swing point, or (b) retest of the hourly OB/FVG zone near 6900–6920.",
    "Step 6: Executed entries targeting 2R, with one target shown at 4960–4970 (on 1m chart) corresponding to ~2.25% move."
  ],
  "outcome": "Trade hit 2R target as shown in frame f022 with annotation 'Target: 2.25 (0.019%) 21, Amount: $1710'.",
  "lessons": "Consolidation breakouts require confirmation via lower-time-frame swing points and candle closures; gaps act as internal liquidity to be filled; 2R is achievable when HTF structure, candle 3 closure, and protected swings align.",
